{{root|en|ine-pro|*peth₂-}}
[[Image:Ballpoint-pen-parts.jpg|thumb|right|A [[ballpoint pen]], showing assembly.]]
From {{inh|en|enm|penne}}, from {{der|en|xno|penne}}, from {{der|en|fro|penne}}, from {{der|en|la|penna||feather}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*péth₂r̥|*péth₂r̥ ~ pth₂én-|feather, wing}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*peth₂-||to rush, fly}} (from which {{m|en|petition}}). Proto-Indo-European base also root of {{m|ine-pro|*petra-}}, from which {{cog|grc|πτερόν||wing}} (whence {{m|en|pterodactyl}}), {{cog|sa|पत्रम्||wing, feather}}, {{cog|cu|перо||pen}}, {{cog|non|fjǫðr}}, {{cog|ang|feðer}} (Modern English {{m|en|feather}});<ref name="oetyld"/> note the /p/ → /f/ Germanic sound change.

See {{m|en|feather}} and {{m|grc|πέτομαι}} for more.

